
// The code snippet demonstrates the use of the [sockets.signal] slot to send a message to a session specified by a reference. It constructs the message using the [strings.concat] slot, and includes an additional argument [type] with a value of "system". The [args] node encapsulates the message details to be transmitted.
sockets.signal:x:@.reference/*/session
   args
      message:x:@strings.concat
      type:system
